description.value: Brass lamp in the form of a standing female panther, with a long, octagonal-sectioned nozzle extending from the chest, terminating in an angular tip with a circular wick-hole. The animal is harnessed and wears a collar with circular pendants. The collar forms the rim of the filling-hole, and is stepped and hinged for a lid, which was formed by the panther's head, now lost. The straps of the harness and the collar are decorated with lozenges and transverse grooves. Suspension-loops (one lost) emerge from the harness on each side of the body; a third suspension-loop may have been placed on the back of the animal, just above the tail, where a cut down patch occurs. A large rectangular repair patch is let into the underside of the body, between the teats. Hinged lid missing. Surface coloration: patchy brown, dark and light green.

description.value: Pottery lamp of the Frog Type, with deep body. Stub-handle at rear. Top decorated with a raised rim round deep-sunk filling-hole area, with head of frog extending from it; below the rim, on each side, are three decorated panels. On the left side the panels are rectangular and contain, respectively, a rosette-circle, a curved rosette, and two opposed s-patterns; on the right, two of the panels are rectangular and one is of truncated triangular shape and they contain a rosette-circle, a curved rosette, and a cross with small patterns, including circles within its arms. Undefined base; impressed below are a transverse line with round terminals, a lozenge containing a circle and an eight-armed cross with round terminals. Flanking the lozenge are the letters ? and I. Brown clay; buff surface. Plaster mould.

Ring-handle at the rear with a rod rising from it to support a handle-ornament in the form of a cross. The cross has knobbed arms (one knob lost) and is surmounted by a dove. Raised rim round the filling-hole, with hinge-pieces at the rear, holding, with an iron pin, a scallop-shell-shaped lamp-lid. Tall cylindrical base with a moulded foot. Within the base is an inserted plate, with a circular hole (repeated in the bottom of the oil-chamber) for the lost sleeve of a pricket-socket. The hole has traces of solder at its edges. Surface colouration: dark brown over bare metal.

description.value: Mould-made pottery lamp with a level top, defined by two mouldings, extending to a wick-hole in its blunt tip; there is no filling-hole. The underbody is decorated with a row of large impressed points, below which is a volute pattern. At its rear rises a stem in the form of a column, surmounted by a duck's head. Standing on top of the lamp and leaning against the column is a figure of an Amazon (or possibly Athena) with an oval shield, wearing a short tunic and a helmet or Phrygian cap. The lamp has a small raised oval base.
